&lt;h2&gt;The Opportunity&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;color: !important;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #000000;&quot;&gt;At ESW, we help the world&#39;s most ambitious brands sell across borders and we&#39;re good at it because we go deep. Deep on the markets, deep on the buyers, deep on the operational mechanics that make global commerce actually work. Our marketing team doesn&#39;t just support the business; it shapes how the world sees us and how our customers understand what&#39;s possible.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;color: !important;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #000000;&quot;&gt;We&#39;re looking for a Director, Product Marketing to help us tell that story better and to build the systems, content, and team that make it stick. This role reports to the VP of Marketing.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;color: !important;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #000000;&quot;&gt;This is a senior, visible role with real influence. You&#39;ll sit at the intersection of product, sales, and marketing, translating what we build into messages that move buyers, enable sellers, and build the ESW brand in the market. You don&#39;t need to have worked in ecommerce or cross-border commerce before but you need to be curious about it and willing to get fluent fast.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #000000;&quot;&gt;What Y&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #000000;&quot;&gt;ou&#39;ll Own&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Positioning and messaging for ESW’s products, ensuring clarity, credibility, and relevance for our target buyers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive alignment across the commercial organisation, working closely with Product, Sales, Client Success, and Marketing to ensure messaging is consistently adopted and used&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead go-to-market strategy for new products and major updates, ensuring launches are coordinated, impactful, and effective from day one&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a strategic partner to Product, bringing market insight, buyer intelligence, and competitive context to help shape product priorities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain deep market and competitive intelligence to inform positioning, sales narratives, and differentiation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and evolve ideal customer profiles (ICPs) and buyer personas across regions, verticals, and buying roles, ensuring usability across the organisation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop sales enablement assets that get used, including pitch decks, battle cards, and case studies, created in close collaboration with Sales&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead product launches and campaigns end-to-end in partnership with demand generation, content, and digital teams to drive pipeline impact&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define success metrics for Product Marketing and work with Marketing Operations to track performance, generate insight, and drive continuous improvement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #000000;&quot;&gt;What We&#39;re Looking For&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep product marketing experience with a proven track record of owning positioning, sales enablement, and product launches at a senior level&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in ecommerce or cross-border commerce, or strong curiosity is a nice-to-have&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong ability to simplify complexity, translating market dynamics and product capabilities into compelling, buyer-centric messaging&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated strength in both strategic thinking and hands-on execution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A collaborative, trust-building working style with Product, Sales, and senior leadership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analytical rigor - you make decisions with data and know how to find the signal in the noise&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;About ESW&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot

&lt;div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;paragraph-in-scc-markdown-text ___1ngh792 ftgm304 f1iaxwol&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Payroll Specialist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;paragraph-in-scc-markdown-text ___1ngh792 ftgm304 f1iaxwol&quot;&gt;The Payroll Specialist is responsible for the accurate, compliant, and timely delivery of payroll and benefits administration across multiple jurisdictions. This role partners closely with Finance, HR, employees, external vendors, and contractor providers to ensure an excellent employee experience, full compliance with statutory and company requirements, and a continuous focus on process improvement and operational excellence.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;___ccc16d0 fje8fi8 f1ng9h0j f1bwykku f18jd3zf&quot;&gt;Process payroll across multiple jurisdictions, ensuring accurate and timely payments, payroll changes, accruals, overtime, bonuses, and reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;___ccc16d0 fje8fi8 f1ng9h0j f1bwykku f18jd3zf&quot;&gt;Administer employee benefits programs, including healthcare, pensions, and other regional benefit schemes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;___ccc16d0 fje8fi8 f1ng9h0j f1bwykku f18jd3zf&quot;&gt;Manage payroll and benefits queries, providing excellent customer service and resolving issues in a timely manner.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;___ccc16d0 fje8fi8 f1ng9h0j f1bwykku f18jd3zf&quot;&gt;Maintain relationships with payroll, benefits, and contractor service providers, ensuring effective service delivery and compliance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;___ccc16d0 fje8fi8 f1ng9h0j f1bwykku f18jd3zf&quot;&gt;Support employee onboarding by providing payroll and benefits guidance to new hires.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;___ccc16d0 fje8fi8 f1ng9h0j f1bwykku f18jd3zf&quot;&gt;Prepare payroll-related financial documentation, including journals, invoices, purchase orders, and audit support.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;___ccc16d0 fje8fi8 f1ng9h0j f1bwykku f18jd3zf&quot;&gt;Maintain payroll and benefits resources on the company intranet, promoting employee self-service and process efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;___ccc16d0 fje8fi8 f1ng9h0j f1bwykku f18jd3zf&quot;&gt;Contribute to process improvements, system enhancements, new vendor implementations, and benefits harmonisation initiatives across regions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Requirements&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Mandatory:&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;paragraph-in-scc-markdown-text ___1ngh792 ftgm304 f1iaxwol&quot;&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years&#39; experience in high-volume payroll processing in Ireland, managing multiple priorities with overlapping deadlines.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience using payroll systems such as CloudPay or similar payroll software.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of payroll, benefits administration, and statutory compliance requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced Excel skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent numerical, analytical, and problem-solving abilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong written and verbal communication skills with exceptional attention to detail. Ability to explain complex payroll concepts to non-payroll stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven commitment to delivering excellent customer service to employees and stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to deliver work within agreed timelines while maintaining accuracy. High level of personal accountability, professionalism, and discretion.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong stakeholder management skills with the ability to build effective relationships at all levels of the organisation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Nice-to-have:&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;IPASS qualification (or equivalent)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Additional qualification in HR, Business Studies, or a related discipline is desirable.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p

&lt;h2 id=&quot;x_the-opportunity&quot;&gt;The Opportunity&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ESW is a dynamic and innovative leader in the DTC ecommerce space, dedicated to delivering high-quality products and services to our clients. The Regional Partnership Account Manager will be responsible for managing and developing relationships with key partners in the assigned region. This role involves identifying new partnership opportunities, facilitating collaboration, and ensuring the success of partner initiatives to achieve mutual business objectives. This role reports directly to the Senior Director of Partnerships.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;x_responsibilities&quot;&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and recruit new partners to expand the company&#39;s partner network in the region.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and execute strategies for partner engagement and growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cultivate and maintain strong relationships with existing partners, acting as the main point of contact for partner inquiries and support.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure alignment between partners and the company&#39;s commercial goals and objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track and analyze partner performance metrics, providing insights and recommendations to optimize partnership effectiveness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct regular business reviews with partners to assess progress and identify areas for improvement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with partners to develop joint marketing strategies, sales enablement programs, and co-branded initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Facilitate training, enablement, and resources for partners to enhance their knowledge about ESW services and support the company&#39;s offerings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay informed about industry trends, competitive landscapes, and partner dynamics in the region.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utilize market insights to refine partnership strategies and identify new opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with internal teams, including sales, marketing, and product development, to ensure successful execution of partner initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Share partner feedback and insights with relevant teams to inform product and service enhancements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate records of partner interactions, performance, and activities within the company&#39;s CRM system.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare and present regular reports on partnership progress and outcomes to senior management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
